</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[146,248,1511,1535]" box="[146,248,1511,1535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">
<emphasis box="[146,248,1511,1535]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Affinities</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[146,1103,1552,1706]" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Buhl, 2003" authorityName="Buhl" authorityYear="2003" box="[272,524,1552,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fennica">
<emphasis box="[272,386,1552,1576]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">P. fennica</emphasis>
Buhl, 2003
</taxonomicName>
, but this species has head more narrowed behind eyes, occiput stronger striated, marginal cilia of wings shorter, and T3–T6 longer than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Buhl" authorityYear="2009" box="[237,340,1617,1641]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nixoni">
<emphasis box="[237,340,1617,1641]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">P. nixoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with hairs in shallow punctures only, and coxae in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Buhl" authorityYear="2003" box="[946,1058,1617,1641]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fennica">
<emphasis box="[946,1058,1617,1641]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">P. fennica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are darkened. 
<taxonomicName authority="Buhl, 1994" authorityName="Buhl" authorityYear="1994" box="[267,512,1649,1673]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavata">
<emphasis box="[267,380,1649,1673]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">P. clavata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Buhl PN" box="[389,512,1649,1673]" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" pagination="329 - 36" refId="ref4563" refString="Buhl PN. 1994. Three new species of Platygaster Latreille, 1809 from Europe. Entomofauna, Z Entomol. 15: 329 - 36." type="journal article" year="1994">Buhl, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has female antennae shorter than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Buhl" authorityYear="2009" box="[942,1044,1649,1673]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nixoni">
<emphasis box="[942,1044,1649,1673]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">P. nixoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and T2 less striated. 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson, 1859" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1859" box="[335,661,1681,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chloropus">
<emphasis box="[335,475,1682,1706]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">P. chloropus</emphasis>
Thomson, 1859
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Buhl, 2006" authorityName="Buhl" authorityYear="2006" box="[722,992,1681,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indefinita">
<emphasis box="[722,860,1682,1706]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">P. indefinita</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Buhl PN" box="[869,992,1681,1705]" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" pagination="127 - 167" refId="ref4784" refString="Buhl PN. 2006. Key to Platygaster (Hymenoptera, Platygastridae) from Denmark, with descriptions of new species. Steenstrupia 29: 127 - 167." type="journal article" year="2006">Buhl, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
have less
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[213,1169,168,225]" pageId="5" pageNumber="691">
striated occiput and hairs on apical tergites inserted in less deep punctures, cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Buhl PN" pageId="5" pageNumber="691" pagination="127 - 167" refId="ref4784" refString="Buhl PN. 2006. Key to Platygaster (Hymenoptera, Platygastridae) from Denmark, with descriptions of new species. Steenstrupia 29: 127 - 167." type="journal article" year="2006">Buhl (2006)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[213,334,282,306]" box="[213,334,282,306]" pageId="5" pageNumber="691">
<emphasis box="[213,334,282,306]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="691">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[213,516,322,346]" box="[213,516,322,346]" pageId="5" pageNumber="691">Named after the collector.</paragraph>
